    "costs": null,
    "actions_taken": [
      "Injured party assisted to facility Medic",
      "Medical evacuation via SAR helicopter to University of Texas Medical Branch",
      "MRI imaging performed on 27-Jan-2016",
      "Knee surgery performed on 10-Feb-2016",
      "Physical therapy scheduled for 24-Feb-2016"
    ],
    "summary": "On 24-Jan-2016 at approximately 1600 hours, an employee at Fieldwood Energy's East Breaks 165 'A' facility inadvertently stepped on a 2-inch pipe approximately 28 inches long that was improperly stored in the East well bay. The pipe rolled out from under the employee's left foot, causing a hyperextension injury to the left knee. Subsequent MRI imaging revealed a Lateral and Medial Meniscus tear requiring surgical repair. Total recovery time estimated at 8 weeks.",
